'''Kisa Shrine''' (きさじんじゃ) is a {{ill|lt=Shinto shrine|Q845945|qid=Q845945|1=Shinto shrine}} located in Maisaka Town, Chūō Ward, Hamamatsu City, Shizuoka Prefecture.

=== Enshrined Deities ===
* {{ill|lt=Kisagaihime・Umugihime|Q11296639|qid=Q11296639|lt=Akagai-hime no Mikoto|1=Kisagaihime and Umugihime}} – Goddess of ark clams
* {{ill|lt=Kisagaihime・Umugihime|Q11296639|qid=Q11296639|lt=Hamagai-hime no Mikoto|1=Kisagaihime and Umugihime}} – Goddess of clams

=== Overview ===
[[File:Kis-jinja.jpg|thumb|<center>Torii gate of Kisa Shrine</center>]]
In the ''{{ill|lt=Engishiki Jinmyōchō|Q11064932|qid=Q11064932|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō}}'' (927), it is listed as “one of the six shrines of Shikichi District among the sixty-two shrines of {{ill|lt=Tōtōmi Province|Q1048864|qid=Q1048864|1=Tōtōmi Province}},” making it a {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Shikinaisha|1=Shikinaisha|qid=Q134917286}}. In addition to serving as the local tutelary shrine, it has long been revered by fishermen as a guardian deity of fisheries and fishing<ref>{{Cite web|Japanese
  |author = Kisa Shrine
  |url = https://www.kisa-jinja.jp/about
  |title = History of Kisa Shrine
  |accessdate = 2016-07-31 }}</ref>.

=== History ===
The shrine was washed away along with the village of Maisawa by the tsunami of the {{ill|lt=Meiō|Q1193841|qid=Q1193841|1=Meiō}} era (1498). However, when the divine shrine washed ashore in the pine grove to the east (the present location), a shrine building was constructed there and the deity was enshrined.

The main hall was rebuilt in {{ill|lt=Tenshō|Q1145058|qid=Q1145058|1=Tenshō (Momoyama period)}} 2 (1574). In {{ill|lt=Keichō|Q1328185|qid=Q1328185|1=Keichō}} 6 (1601), three koku of land bearing an ink seal were granted by Ina Bizen-no-kami, and thereafter five koku bearing vermilion seals were granted by the third shogun {{ill|lt=Tokugawa Iemitsu|Q314481|qid=Q314481|1=Tokugawa Iemitsu}} and successive shoguns.

In {{ill|lt=Meiji|Q3125096|qid=Q3125096|1=Meiji era}} 6, the shrine was ranked as a {{ill|lt=Gōsha|Q134917316|qid=Q134917316|1=Gō-sha}}. In {{ill|lt=Taishō|Q329174|qid=Q329174|1=Taishō era}} 1, the main hall was constructed, and in {{ill|lt=Taishō|Q329174|qid=Q329174|1=Taishō era}} 13 it was designated as a shrine eligible to receive offerings of sacred food and ritual expenses<ref>{{Cite web|Japanese
  |author = Shizuoka Prefecture Association of Shinto Shrines
  |url = http://shizuoka-jinjacho.or.jp/shokai/jinja.php?id=4413057
  |title = Kisa Shrine
  |accessdate = 2016-07-31 }}</ref>.

A restoration project in Heisei 22 carried out the raising and realignment of the main hall, as well as re-roofing the worship hall and protective structures with tiles.

=== Subsidiary Shrines ===
The subsidiary and related shrines within the precincts are as follows.

'''Precinct Shrines'''
* Goshinsama (Guardian Deity / Ancestral Deity): Enshrines Tenpaku Shrine and divided spirits from Ise Grand Shrine, Tsushima Shrine, and Kasuga Taisha.
